node.title: Nervous wait across Sydney and Central Coast after Omicron COVID exposures
node.description: People who have been to almost a dozen exposure sites across Sydney and the NSW Central Coast face a nervous wait to see if they've contracted theÂ Omicron strain of COVID-19.
node.content:
["People who have been to almost a dozen exposure sites across Sydney and the NSW Central Coast face a nervous wait to see if they've contracted the\u00a0Omicron strain of COVID-19.", "Health authorities yesterday confirmed a traveller from southern Africa, and the fifth NSW confirmed case of the latest variant, had spent at least two days in the community while\u00a0infectious.", "A woman in her 30s who landed\u00a0in Sydney on Thursday, before new travel restrictions were in place, had visited at least two southern African countries before arriving in Australia.", "Contact tracing determined the fully-vaccinated woman visited several retails stores in Sydney's west and fast food outlets in the Central Coast.", "The woman is now isolating at home in the Central Coast.", "Anyone who attended these\u00a0venues in Parramatta and on\u00a0the Central Coast at the following times is a\u00a0casual contact who must immediately get tested and isolate until a negative result is received.", "Friday, November 26:", "Saturday, November 27:", "Anyone who was on the flight is considered a close contact and will need to get tested immediately for COVID-19 and isolate for 14 days, regardless of their vaccination status.", "\"Please get tested even if you have had a test in recent days. If you test result is negative, please continue to monitor for symptoms and if any symptoms appear, get tested and isolate again,\" a NSW Health spokesperson said.", "NSW Health said a\u00a0person now residing in Broken Hill who was on the same flight from Doha was\u00a0unlikely to have been infected with the Omicron variant but was\u00a0still isolating at home.", "Genomic sequencing is still underway to probe whether one other confirmed COVID-19 case from that flight has\u00a0the Omicron variant.", "The World Health Organization (WHO) has classified Omicron as a \"variant of concern\" but said further research was\u00a0needed to assess its potential to escape protection against immunity induced by vaccines and previous infections.", "Health Minister Greg Hunt this morning said the government's \"overwhelming view\" was that the Omicron variant was \"manageable\" and the health advice was that it may be milder than other variants.", "", "
Heavily mutated Omicron variant puts scientist on alert
"]
